'''馬蹄鐵理論'''（{{lang-en|The Horseshoe theory}}）是一個由[[法國|法國]][[哲學家|哲學家]][[让-皮埃尔·费伊|让-皮埃尔·费伊]]提出的，描述[[政治學|政治]]上[[極左派|極左派]]和[[極右派|極右派]]的關係的理論。其認為，極左派和極右派並非傳統政治直線軸上的兩個[[極端|極端]]，反而是像[[馬蹄鐵|馬蹄鐵]]的兩個極端一般——兩派其實有很多相似的地方<ref>{{cite news |first=Frédéric |last=Encel |author2=Thual, François |title=United States-Israel: A friendship that needs to be demystified |url=http://www.ufppc.org/content/view/1751/2/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930160218/http://www.ufppc.org/content/view/1751/2/ |archive-date=2007-09-30 |quote=Jean-Pierre Faye's famous horseshoe theory (according to which extremes meet) finds verification here more than in other places, and the two states of delirium often mingle and meet, unfortunately spreading beyond these extremist circles. But contrary to the legend deliberately maintained and/or the commonplace believed in good faith, Israel and the United States have not always been allies; on several occasions their relations have even been strained. |work=[[费加罗报|Le Figaro]] |location=Paris |date=2004-11-13|access-date=2009-02-13 }}</ref>。

馬蹄鐵理論和傳統的[[左派和右派|政治學直線軸]]和[[政治光譜|政治光譜]]幾乎互相[[矛盾|矛盾]]。而馬蹄鐵理論的支持者則以極左和極右主張極為相似作為論點，例如近年在極左和極右陣營裡都出現[[反猶太主義|反猶太主義]]的聲音。<ref>{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|coauthors=|title=The Political Horseshoe again|url=http://www.aijac.org.au/review/2006/31-11/scribb31-11.htm|quote=I think Mr. Loewenstein has done a good job demonstrating why many people believe, as the “political horseshoe” theory states, that there is a lot more common ground between the far left, where Loewenstein dwells politically, and the far right views of someone like Betty Luks than people on the left would care to admit.|work=[[AIJAC|AIJAC]]|date=|accessdate=2009-02-13|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516212834/http://www.aijac.org.au/review/2006/31-11/scribb31-11.htm|archivedate=2011-05-16}}</ref>

而世界最大的策略諮詢服務公司[[羅蘭貝格咨詢公司|羅蘭貝格咨詢公司]]的研究員約瑟夫·約菲 (Josef Joffe)在一篇[[論文|論文]]中指出：

{{cquote|[[全球化|全球化]]的進程能否度過陰霾呢？事實上，在2008年[[金融海嘯|金融海嘯]]以前就已經有[[反全球化|反全球化]]的起事；而早在這個年代的中段，[[民粹|民粹]]派已經在展現他們憤怒的面容。而最富戲劇性的例子，是在[[德國|德國]]和[[奧地利|奧地利]]，[[民粹主義|民粹主義]][[政黨|政黨]]憑藉[[孤立主義|孤立主義]]、[[保護主義|保護主義]]和資源重新分配的政綱，取得[[選舉|選舉]]上的大勝。在德國，是一個[[左翼民粹主|左翼民粹主]]义政黨（[[德国左翼党|德国左翼党]]）；而在奧地利，則是一組總得票率達30%的右翼政黨。這裡左右派又再次體現了現代政治的「馬蹄鐵」理論：當鋼鐵被扭曲時，兩個尾端近得幾乎可以互相接觸。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rolandberger.com/news/2008-12-22-rbsc-news-NewYearEssay.html |title=New Year’s Essay 2009 - For Roland Berger |accessdate=2009-04-19 |author=Josef Joffe |date=2008-12-22 |work= |publisher=Roland Berger |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090203054730/http://www.rolandberger.com/news/2008-12-22-rbsc-news-NewYearEssay.html |archivedate=2009-02-03 }} </ref>}} 


而據《政治學家》（Political Science Scholar）網站，馬蹄鐵理論被列為有效和重要的[[政治學|政治學]][[名詞|名詞]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://politicalsciencescholar.com/political-science-terms/|title=Political Science Terms|accessdate=2009-04-19|author=|date=|work=|publisher=Political Science Scholar|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090303124228/http://politicalsciencescholar.com/political-science-terms/|archivedate=2009-03-03}}</ref>

== 批評 ==
事實上有不少[[社會學家|社會學家]]認為，馬蹄鐵理論是不可信的。<ref>Political Research Associates: [http://www.publiceye.org/study_right.html Study the U.S. Political Right] {{Wayback|url=http://www.publiceye.org/study_right.html |date=20090202064047 }}</ref>而瑞德大學（University of Reading）學者巴克（Peter Barker）<ref>[[University_of_Reading|University of Reading]]: [http://www.reading.ac.uk/Languages/about/staff/p-j-barker.asp Peter Barker]{{Dead link|date=2019年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>在自己所著的書《[[民主德國|民主德國]]和其歷史 》（GDR and Its History）中，引述谢菲尔德大學湯遜（Peter Thompson）的批評，認為馬蹄鐵理論<ref>[[University_of_Sheffield|University of Sheffield]]: [http://www.shef.ac.uk/german/staff/profiles/pthompson/index.html Peter Thompson] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090101013005/http://www.shef.ac.uk/german/staff/profiles/pthompson/index.html |date=2009-01-01 }}</ref>扭曲了左右派政治主張不同的距離，更不滿意這個理論無法打破傳統的政治學直線軸，相類似主張之間連貫性。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=eo9vSXdn2CAC&pg=PA103&lpg=PA103&dq=%22horseshoe+theory%22+politics&source=web&ots=NGPgOLI7V1&sig=9_cj_uXTIlmFup5ZKjZFMQfSQjw&hl=en&ei=e8CMSfvIOMa-kAXh8p2uDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=9&ct=result |title=GDR and Its History pp103 |access-date=2009-04-19 |archive-date=2012-10-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023062348/http://books.google.com.au/books?id=eo9vSXdn2CAC&pg=PA103&lpg=PA103&dq=%22horseshoe+theory%22+politics&source=web&ots=NGPgOLI7V1&sig=9_cj_uXTIlmFup5ZKjZFMQfSQjw&hl=en&ei=e8CMSfvIOMa-kAXh8p2uDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&resnum=9&ct=result |dead-url=no }}</ref>.

